&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hovercraft is a dynamic and innovative creative design firm that partners with brands to craft compelling experiences through design, strategy, and technology. We specialize in creating standout visuals, interactive digital content, and impactful branding solutions that push the boundaries of creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are on the hunt for someone whose conceptual thinking and aesthetic is as provocative as it is progressive. You are brand-forward yet able to deliver across multiple mediums: interactive installations, spatial environments, brand stunts, digital experiences, animation graphics. You dream big while stay grounded in reality. You&amp;nbsp;always&amp;nbsp;push the work beyond the expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold the line on aesthetics and craft while thinking conceptually and strategically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt to various brand styles, yet always identify opportunities to add unexpected interactive, environmental, and animation elements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with (and sometimes drive) design teams of 2-4 people per project. You’ll need to keep them in check and the quality high.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present your work confidently, communicate project progress with clarity, and be ready to convince internal teams, clients, and vendors why your approach is the right one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exploit the latest tech, platforms, and generative AI to break new ground. We’re not here to do what’s been done before.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep a finger on the pulse of industry trends and emerging tech, so the work stays sharp and forward-thinking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive design experience from an agency or design studio, backed by a portfolio that shows off good taste and inventive, boundary-pushing work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A conceptual dynamo who can maintain high-level design standards across everything you touch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of established and emerging technologies—so you can not only talk the talk but also use them to create innovative experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who is willing to bend the brief to deliver something beyond what was asked for.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You hit deadlines, juggle multiple projects, and make confident, smart decisions under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborator, but also a driver—someone who’s pro-active, positive, and pushes projects forward autonomously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear and concise communication, especially with remote team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in industry-standard design and collaboration software, including Adobe Creative Suite, Figma, and Slack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;text-node&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;The salary range for this position is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;starts at $100 hourly&lt;/strong&gt;. Hourly rate is determined by a combination of factors that include qualifications, applicable skills, relevant experience and other budgetary considerations such as location/geography.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;text-node&quot;&gt;Hovercraft is a remote-first company, working primarily on Pacific and Mountain time. You must be eligible to work in the US as a 1099 contractor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recruitment Notice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We use AI-assisted tools solely to help identify and highlight keywords related to critical design skills and relevant experience within applications. These tools support our recruiting team by improving consistency and efficiency; they do not make hiring decisions. All applications are reviewed by humans, and AI is not used in a discriminatory manner or to evaluate personal characteristics unrelated to job requirements.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt

&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hovercraft is a dynamic and innovative creative design firm that partners with brands to craft compelling experiences through design, strategy, and technology. We specialize in creating standout visuals, interactive digital content, and impactful branding solutions that push the boundaries of creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hovercraft is looking for an Associate Creative Director to lead conceptual and design duties for our Experience Team. The ideal candidate has strong creative instinct, refined leadership skills and is as comfortable in front of clients as they are in front of a virtual white board. You can push the boundaries of what’s possible while giving clients the confidence that our vision and recommendations will be successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACDs at Hovercraft lead by example and drive projects forward by rolling up their sleeves and actively participating in their development. Days will be spent working closely with, and leading your design team&amp;nbsp;to conceptualize and develop digitally-driven projects ranging from immersive environments, progressive UI, augmented reality, and 3D brand animations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a deep knowledge of progressive experience design principles, emerging technologies and the production techniques, and implications, of your ideas. As the creative lead, you will advocate for the design team by working closely with production, development, and animation leads in our Experience group to help ensure that projects reach their full potential and are executed on time and on budget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide creative leadership and oversight of projects from inception to delivery, with a focus on those that are highly creative and/or strategic in nature.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and mentor designers, art directors and specialists while actively engaged in projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present work and communicate project development in an articulate and efficient manner to internal teams, clients and vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with clients to distill their asks and agenda’s into actionable, strategic briefs for Hovercraft creative teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inter-departmental collaboration with other leads for internal alignment of best practices and knowledge sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Producers and Executive Producers to determine project staff plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report to senior creative leads (Creative Director).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ Years proven experience with a strong design background in an agency or studio setting, with a well-rounded portfolio of immersive, interactive and animation projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Progressive creative vision, with strengths in concept and narrative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding and active engagement with emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to direct small and large teams in both remote and in-person settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate effectively with Producers and keep creative development on brief.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive and self-actualization to make an impact on the team and projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative team player that is highly motivated, proactive and positive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organization and time management skills to stay on task &amp;amp; deadline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working on a variety of projects with varying timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
